1. Added Retry Logic in rest_utils.py
Changes Made:

Introduced a helper function make_request_with_retry to handle retry logic with exponential backoff and jitter.
Modified the existing do_post and do_put functions to use this helper function, ensuring they retry requests on failure.
Files Modified:

rest_utils.py
How It Works:

The make_request_with_retry function attempts a request multiple times if it fails, increasing the delay between attempts to avoid overloading the server.
The do_post and do_put functions now wrap their HTTP request logic with this retry mechanism, making them robust against temporary failures of the PlainID admin URL.
2. Updated rest_server.py to Use do_post and do_put
Changes Made:

Ensured all interactions with the PlainID admin URL in rest_server.py use the retry-enabled do_post and do_put functions from rest_utils.py.
Added health check functionality to monitor the availability of the PlainID admin URL and attempt to reconnect if it goes down.
Files Modified:

rest_server.py
How It Works:

The check_admin_url function sends a health check request to the admin URL using do_post and retries on failure.
The run_health_checks function runs in a separate thread to periodically check the admin URL’s health and reconnect if needed.
Other parts of rest_server.py that interact with the PlainID admin URL use do_post and do_put, ensuring all requests benefit from the retry logic.
